
# Development Guide

> **First-time setup?** See [ONBOARDING.md](ONBOARDING.md) for tool installation
> and [SETUP.md](SETUP.md) for project configuration.

This guide covers the **daily development workflow** after initial setup.

## Environment Configuration

Copy `.env.example` to `.env` and configure:

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

Replace all `__CHANGE_ME__` placeholders (especially secrets) before using shared environments.

For non-local workflows, copy `.env.example` to the appropriate env file and adjust
the values listed in the "Per-Environment Quick Reference" section at the bottom:

```bash
cp .env.example .env.dev       # shared development server
cp .env.example .env.test      # CI/integration testing
cp .env.example .env.staging   # pre-production validation
cp .env.example .env.prod      # production deployment baseline
```

Keep these files aligned and prefer one canonical active env file per run target.

Local best practices:

- Keep shared local defaults in `.env`
- Put machine-specific backend overrides in `.env.local` (start from `.env.local.example`)
- Put machine-specific frontend overrides in `frontend/.env.local` (start from `frontend/.env.local.example`)
- Never commit `.env*` runtime files

Runtime safety note: staging and production settings disable dotenv loading,
so those environments depend on explicit process/container environment variables.

Key variables:

| Variable | Description | Default |
|----------|-------------|---------|
| `{{ project_slug | upper }}_ENVIRONMENT` | Environment name | `local` |
| `{{ project_slug | upper }}_DEBUG` | Enable debug mode | `false` |
| `{{ project_slug | upper }}_DATABASE_URL` | Database connection URL | *(see .env.example)* |
{% if use_redis %}
| `{{ project_slug | upper }}_REDIS_URL` | Redis connection URL | `redis://localhost:6379/0` |
{% endif %}

