### Workflow Checkpointers

LangGraph workflows store execution state in a checkpointer. See
[SETUP.md](SETUP.md#workflow-checkpointers) for the full backend comparison table
(Memory / SQLite / PostgreSQL).

During development, the in-memory checkpointer is used by default (no
persistence across restarts). To test durable workflows locally,
switch to the SQLite checkpointer:

```bash
export {{ project_slug | upper }}_CHECKPOINTER_BACKEND=sqlite
```
{%- endif %}

## Testing

```bash
task test               # Run default tests (registry + unit + property + frontend)
task backend:test       # Backend tests only
task frontend:test:unit # Frontend tests only
```

See [TESTING.md](TESTING.md) for the full testing guide (markers, directories,
coverage, property-based tests, performance tests).

## Linting and Formatting

```bash
task lint               # Lint all code
task format             # Format all code
task typecheck          # Run type checking
```

## Pre-commit Hooks

Install hooks:

```bash
pre-commit install
pre-commit install --hook-type commit-msg
```

Run all hooks manually:

```bash
pre-commit run --all-files
```
